heya hebim li dinyê, ez ê ji derdî wara bêjim.
 
as long as I am in this world, I will speak of these pains.

15
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Hunermend im çi bêjim, bi derd û kul dinalim,
 
I am an artist, what can I say, I groan with pain and
sorrow,

16
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:40,000
heya hebim li dinyê, ez ê ji derdî wara bêjim.
 
as long as I am in this world, I will speak of these pains.

17
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:44,000
Belê, belê, temaşevanên hêja. Dema we xweş be.
 
Yes, yes, esteemed viewers. Have a good time.

18
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:48,000
Îro jî em li navçeya Mabetan e.
 
Today too, we are in the district of Mabeta.

19
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:51,000
Îro jî, bernameya me li ser gundê Omo ye.
 
Today too, our program is about the village of Omo.

20
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Lê em spasîya zaroka dikin, zarokên vî gundî dikin,
 
But we thank the children, the children of this village,

21
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:59,000
bi stranên xweş bernameya me vekirin.
 
they opened our program with beautiful songs.

22
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:19,000
Di vê hefteyê de jî, em ê bi hev re gundê Omo nas bikin.
 
In this week too, we will get to know the village of Omo
together.

23
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:13,000
Belê, îro jî em li gundê Omo ne.
 
Yes, today too we are in the village of Omo.

24
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,000
Dayîkan jî xwest tişkî ji me re çêbikin.
 
The mothers also wanted to make something for us.

25
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:18,000
Niha jî bihar e.
 
Now it is spring.

26
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:24,000
Dema mast e, şîr e, penêr e. Masta kemandî ye, ev gelek tişt
di şîr çêdibin.
 
It's the season for yogurt, milk, and cheese. It's aged
yogurt, many things are made from milk.

27
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:29,000
Niha jî dayîka ji me re xwest tişkî çêbikin, em ê bi hev re
nas bikin.
 
Now the mother wanted to make something for us, we will get
to know it together.

28
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Merheba jinap, dayê.
 
Hello auntie, mother.

29
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,000
Ehlen wesehlen.
 
Welcome.

30
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Dayê, destên we sax bin.
 
Mother, bless your hands.

31
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Ete jî sax be.
 
Bless yours too.

32
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:38,000
Niha ka hûn çi çêdikin? Ka ji me re, ji temaşevanan re
bêjin.
 
Now, what are you making? Tell us, and the viewers.

33
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:44,000
Ê de em çi çêdikin qurban? Da em mastê xwe dikelînin, em
pezê xwe didoşin.
 
Well, what are we making dear? We are boiling our yogurt, we
are milking our sheep.

34
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:47,000
Da em malê xwe rûştin, malê xwe şên dikin.
 
So we furnish our home, we liven up our home.

35
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:54,000
De, inha em kelînin, em ê dînin erdê, em ê têkin qatremîzê
xwe.
 
So, now we boil it, we will put it down, we will put it in
our jars.

36
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:58,000
Ê paşê lêxin zivistanê... em ê zeytê xwe ser kin û zivistanê
xwe ra hildin.
 
Then we will keep it for winter... we will pour our oil on
it and keep it for winter.

37
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,000
Ev masta kemandî ye?
 
Is this aged yogurt?

38
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:01,000
Ev mastê kemandî ye.
 
This is aged yogurt.

39
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:04,000
Naha em, bi hesabê behsa mast bikin. Di vê demê de çi
çêdibe?
 
Now let's talk about the yogurt. What is made during this
season?

40
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:08,000
Di vê demê de, penêr, mast, di vê demê de, heta payîzê
genim...
 
In this season, cheese, yogurt, in this season, until autumn
wheat...

41
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:11,000
Ê ka ji min re bêje, we niha çi çêdikir?
 
So tell me, what were you making now?

42
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:15,000
Penêr e, mast e. E... îşte... genim e.
 
It's cheese, yogurt. Um... well... it's wheat.

43
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:19,000
Ê... we em ê biçinin em ê genimê xwe bikelînin. Didaniyê
xwe.
 
Well... we will harvest, we will boil our wheat. Our boiled
wheat.

44
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:21,000
Pilxurê xwe çêkin, bikutin.
 
Make our bulgur, pound it.

45
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:25,000
Bihêrin ji malê xwe kin zivistanê xwe bixwin.
 
Grind it to keep it at home and eat it in the winter.

46
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:28,000
Naha mastê kemandî çawa çêdibe?
 
Now, how is aged yogurt made?

47
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:31,000
Em... em ê... karên... pezê xwe biddoşin.
 
We... we will... milk our sheep.

48
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,000
Em ê di birûşê xwe kin.
 
We will put it in our pots.

49
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:35,000
Ê cîran û kî em ê dido be bi hev re bikin.
 
Neighbors and whoever, we will do it together.

50
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:38,000
Em ê şîrê xwe bidin dorên xwe.
 
We will give our milk for our turns.

51
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:41,000
Em ê wan şîrê xwe, kir penêrê xwe, kir mast, em hildin.
 
We will take that milk, make it into cheese, make it into
yogurt, and keep it.

52
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:44,000
Dûre amên... ev wan... hazirta wîn...
 
Then we come... these... their preparations...

53
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:50,000
Em penêr kin, penêrê xwe dînin xwê kin, dî leganê de. Bêlin
di ro sê ro.
 
We make cheese, we salt our cheese, put it in a basin. We
leave it for two, three days.

54
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:53,000
Paşê sîravka xwe çêkin, berdin ser.
 
Then we make our brine, pour it over it.

55
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:59,000
Pêşî hazir... em gazê xwe dînin û birûşê xwe dînin û penêrê
xwe çêkin...
 
First ready... we set up our stove and put our pot and make
our cheese...

56
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:01,000
Deh pênz deqe em dikelînin.
 
We boil it for ten to fifteen minutes.

57
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:05,000
Her wecbe me keland, penêr germ kir, wecbe kir nava birûş.
 
We boiled each batch, heated the cheese, put the batch into
the pot.

58
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:09,000
Deh pênz deqe... paşê me ew dikişand avdêkê, em ê baş kin...
 
Ten, fifteen minutes... then we drained it in a strainer, we
will clean it well...

59
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:14,000
Da sar bibe. Em ê biqevşin... dînin ser tebsîyê xwe.
 
So it cools down. We squeeze it... put it on our trays.

60
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:20,000
Pak bikin û têkin qatremîzê xwe. Aşê sîravkê xwe çêkin û
berdin serê.
 
Clean it and put it in our jars. Then we make our brine and
pour it over.

61
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,000
Ew malê zivistanê ye wa.
 
This is for the winter supplies.

62
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,000
Him.
 
I see.

63
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:25,000
Ew mastê me jî, em ê têkin tûrê xwe.
 
As for our yogurt, we will put it in our bag.

64
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:29,000
Em... avê berde nav, em xwêya xwe têkinê.
 
We... it releases water inside, we add our salt to it.

65
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:34,000
Ê her ro... heft ro nine, heşt ro nine, deh ro nine, dozdeh
ro nine,
 
And every day... whether it's seven days, eight days, ten
days, twelve days,

66
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:38,000
Wî tûrî em ê pak bişon, paşî... û avê berdinê.
 
We will wash that bag well, then... and pour water on it.

67
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:41,000
Mastê tê de pak sipî bibe wa têkivî.
 
So the yogurt inside becomes pure white.

68
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,000
Paşê em ê boşkî ji tûr...
 
Then we will empty it from the bag...

69
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:45,000
Em ê sîzakek hildin.
 
We will take a strainer.

70
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:52,000
Û em ê wan, arê xwe dadin, di birûşê xwe kin, bigerînin,
bikelînin, û qatremîzê xwe kinê dînin.
 
And we will set up our fire, put it in our pot, stir it,
boil it, and put it in our jars.

71
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,000
Yanî ew dor û wextî wek tûra derxist?
 
Meaning, the time and turn when you took it out of the bag?

72
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:54,000
We mast ro da...
 
Yes.

73
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,000
We mast ro da...
 
You exposed the yogurt to the sun...

74
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Him.
 
Yes.

75
00:06:56,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Erê. Wê rû yê derkê bikeli... paşê tûr dexin.
 
Yes. You take it out and boil it... then put it in the bag.

76
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:03,000
Ê belê dayê, li gundê we pez hebû, pir bû?
 
Well mother, did you have sheep in your village, was there a
lot?

77
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:08,000
E... malê osê, wisa wa hebû, e malê Hemdê hebî, e malê Silo
hebî...
 
Um... the Osê family, they had some like that, the Hemdê
family had, the Silo family had...

78
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:11,000
Ê malê Mihemedê Reşo hebî, Mîradê Reşo hebî.
 
The Mihemedê Reşo family had, Mîradê Reşo had.

79
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:13,000
Ge... pir... xudan pez bûn.
 
They were... a lot... they were flock owners.

80
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:18,000
E pir da... çûn çiyê... pezê xwe dibirin diçûn çiyê... ji
çiyê... ji wextê tişta...
 
Most of them... went to the mountains... they took their
sheep and went to the mountains... from the mountains...
during the times of things...

81
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:23,000
Li wura îşê xwe dikirin. Penîrê xwe, mastî xwe, dobê xwe...
ev tişt dikirin.
 
They would do their work there. Their cheese, their yogurt,
their turns... they did these things.

82
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:26,000
Malê Henenê Hecî dikir.
 
The Henenê Hecî family used to do it.

83
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:28,000
Malê Hemdê dikir.
 
The Hemdê family used to do it.

84
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:31,000
Dê malê Sîno lara jî...
 
And the Sîno family too...

85
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:35,000
Îşte dawara xwe d... na pir. Naka wisa hi.
 
Well, their livestock... not a lot. Now it is like this.

86
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:42,000
Naka na wisa ye, wî çaxî pirtir bû dawarên wan. Xwedî
dikirin, şîr dikirin, didoştin...
 
Now it's not like that, at that time their livestock was
more. They raised them, they produced milk, they milked...

87
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:44,000
Yanî ne dikirin... îşê xwe.
 
I mean they did their work.

88
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,000
Me ji spas da. Em ê vegerin cem te.
 
We thank you too. We will come back to you.

89
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,000
Kamo can wa jî.
 
Go ahead, Kamo dear.

90
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,000
Merheba jinap jî.
 
Hello to you too, auntie.

91
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,000
Ehlen wesehlen bi hatina we.
 
Welcome to you.

92
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,000
Sax be.
 
Bless you.

93
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:53,000
Dayê em tişkî j'te bipirsin.
 
Mother, let us ask you something.

94
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:59,000
Jibon ku... naha dema biharê jî, dema mast e, mastê kemandî
ye, penêr, ewe.
 
Because... now is the spring season, the season for yogurt,
aged yogurt, cheese, etc.

95
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:03,000
Ê bi taybet... hûn j'xwa re çêdikin lê hûn difroşin jî?
 
Especially... do you make it for yourselves or do you sell
it too?

96
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:05,000
Naha dawarên me... kêm in, em j'xwa re çêdikin.
 
Now our livestock... is little, we make it for ourselves.

97
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:07,000
Naha her yik... pezê we çiqas heye?
 
Now each one... how many sheep do you have?

98
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,000
Çar dawaran e... pênc dawaran e wa...
 
It's four animals... five animals...

99
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,000
Him. Hûn çi çêdikin?
 
I see. What do you make?

100
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:12,000
Mast e... penêr e.
 
Yogurt... cheese.

101
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,000
Tenê?
 
Only?

102
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:16,000
Û... vê mastî... sîzme e... gulok dikin... em dikin
xatremîzan.
 
And... this yogurt... we strain it... we make it into
balls... we put it in jars.

103
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,000
Naha em... bikelînin e.
 
Now we... boil it.

104
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,000
Em zeytê bas dikin ser.
 
We press oil on top.

105
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:23,000
E wa.
 
Like this.

106
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,000
Naha pey vê... dema... dema çî ye?
 
Now after this... what is the season for?

107
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:27,000
Piştî ev naha, penêr û mast... di qê... piştî wa çite?
 
After this now, cheese and yogurt... after that what comes?

108
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:33,000
Î... çêkin wara zivistanê bibin... em ê didaniyê bikelînin,
pelxurê çêkin, em îşita çêkin, dere... derat çêkin.
 
We... make these to take into winter... we will boil boiled-
wheat, make bulgur, we make tarhana, make... provisions.

109
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,000
Em me... rakin.
 
We... store them.

110
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:37,000
Eva.
 
This is it.

111
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:40,000
Spas ji bo te jî.
 
Thank you too.

112
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,000
Dayê em tiştekî j'te pirs kin.
 
Mother, let us ask you something.

113
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:48,000
Naha piştî... ev m... mastê xwe çêdikin û penêr e... de.
Piştî wa hûn ê çêkin? Dema çi ye?
 
Now after... making your yogurt and cheese... After that
what will you make? What season is it?

114
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,000
Mesela dora wê cilûrez e.
 
For example, then it's the turn for the grape harvest.

115
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,000
Cilûrez e.
 
The grape harvest.

116
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:55,000
Cilûrez e... em cilûreza xwe bigrin, zêde be... em difroşin.
 
The grape harvest... we harvest the grapes, if it's too
much... we sell it.

117
00:08:55,000 --> 00:09:00,000
Ê mesela di dudo em keben, mesela dimsekî bacan e were.
Dimsekî sota were.
 
And for example secondly we make, for example tomato paste
comes. Pepper paste comes.

118
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:04,000
Em ê wan tiştan çêkin. Dûre zeytûn tên.
 
We will make those things. Then olives come.

119
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:12,000
Em ê zeytûnên xwe... hinarên xwe, zeytûnên xwe biqelasînin,
tiştê xwe hemû çêkin... tiştên xwe giş j'malê çêdikin... em
gişt xwera hildin zivistanê...
 
We will harvest our olives... our pomegranates, we crack our
olives, we make all our things... we make all of it at
home... we keep all of it for winter...

120
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:20,000
Ya me na hecetî... tiştî nen. Û em yane... giş j'malê
çêdibe.
 
We do not need... anything. And we, I mean... everything is
made at home.

121
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:23,000
Spas ji bo te jî. Spas em hatin cem te.
 
Thank you too. Thank you, we came to you.

122
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,000
Dayê em hatin cem te. Şikrem j'te bive.
 
Mother, we have come to you. Bless you.

123
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:30,000
Niha wa, wek jin, û... in di gund de hûn çi karî dikin?
 
Now, as women, and... in the village what work do you do?

124
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:37,000
Yanî, ne bes ji bo rû. Yanî jin e vê gundî, winda çi karî
dikin, çi nakin?
 
I mean, not just for this. I mean the women of this village,
what work do they do there, what do they not do?

125
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:42,000
Da em naha... ew... l'malê xwene... karekî nîn e... dexil...
bilxur em ê bilxurê xwe bikelenen.
 
So we now... those... we are at our home... there is no
other work... crops... bulgur, we will boil our bulgur.

126
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:48,000
Dixil... nîsko, noko, firîk, tirşê, filan... em vî tiştî xwa
kin.
 
The crops... lentils, chickpeas, green wheat, sour soup,
etc... we prepare these things.

127
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:52,000
Û doxilmî... mişmişa, em reçelê mişmişa çêdikin. Doxil...
gula... reçelê gula...
 
And also... apricots, we make apricot jam. Also... roses...
rose jam...

128
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:56,000
Zeytûn e wa... em zeytûn... em qerak... e... zeytê xwe
rakin... hema wa.
 
Olives... we harvest olives... we crack them... we store our
oil... just like that.

129
00:09:56,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Ê... îşte tiştê malê hawa, em ne hewceyê tiştekî dibin.
 
And... the things of the house are like this, we do not need
anything else.

130
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:14,000
Êdî anîna xelkê... ewa hajatê bajêr in, bajar gî pîs
derketin. Em yanî me l'gund kêf kirî em bi xwe di nav
gundiyê xwe bin, di nav welatiyê xwe bin, di nav miletê xwe
rûnin, xweş e ji hemûyan.
 
Now the things people bring... those are city things, the
city things all turned out to be bad. We are happy in the
village, we stay among our fellow villagers, we stay among
our compatriots, we sit among our own people, it's better
than everything.

131
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,000
Dayê adê tiştek bipirsim.
 
Mother, let me ask you something.

132
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:18,000
Her tişt ji gund tê bajêra?
 
Does everything come to the city from the village?

133
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

134
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,000
Yanî her tişt di gundan da çêdibe diçe bajêra?
 
So everything is made in the villages and goes to the city?

135
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:24,000
Yanî gund xwe bi xwe îdare dike.
 
I mean, the village sustains itself.

136
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:27,000
Wekî mînak malê da be, her tiştekî xwe ji xwe dertîne?
 
For example, in a household, does it produce everything
itself?

137
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:30,000
Tiştekî mîna bajar li gund tune ye, na.
 
There is nothing like the city in the village, no.

138
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,000
Zebeşê gund gund dertîne, darê zeytûnê dar in,
 
The village produces its watermelons, olive trees are trees,

139
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:36,000
her tiştê ji gund tê bajêra. Ne?
 
everything comes from the village to the city. Right?

140
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:40,000
Gelek spas dayê, em ê dîsa bên ba te.
 
Thank you very much mother, we will come back to you again.

141
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:44,000
Ew xweşikbûna berê, di gundan da maye heta niha?
 
Does that old beauty remain in the villages until now?

142
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:48,000
Ê da... însanên îtîfaq bin, heye, mayî.
 
Well... if people are united, yes, it remains.

143
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:52,000
Û însanên ne îtîfaq bin, na mabe xelas bû çû.
 
And if people are not united, no, it is gone and finished.

144
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:55,000
Ê tiştê berê, çi xera bûye ji wê nema ye?
 
What from the old things got ruined and doesn't remain?

145
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:57,000
Niha îtîfaq li dinyayê nîn e.
 
Now there is no unity in the world.

146
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:58,000
Erê rast e.
 
Yes, that is right.

147
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:00,000
Na bi tifaq e, êdî henek da nîn in qurbano.
 
There is no unity, there are no jokes anymore my dear.

148
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:04,000
Yên rind bûn tifaq bûn, gi tiştî te tifaq bû,
 
Those who were good were united, in everything you were
united,

149
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:08,000
û ti na rind bî gi ne tifaq e. Gi ne rind e.
 
and if you are not good, everything is disunited. Everything
is not good.

150
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:11,000
Ê tiştê berê xweş di gund da çi hebû û niha tunîne, çi ye?
 
And what good things were there in the past in the village
that are not there now? What are they?

151
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:15,000
Tiştê me yê berê xweş, bûk û xwesî yên wêna,
 
Our good things from the past, the bride and mother-in-law
of that time,

152
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:20,000
bûkê gilî xwesiyê xwe nedikira, rind bû.
 
the bride wouldn't complain about her mother-in-law, it was
good.

153
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:23,000
Yekî wê bûkê li wê tunebû.
 
No one had a problem with that bride.

154
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:30,000
Û yekî wê xwesiyê jî bes qencî di sere wî bûkê qet gileyê wî
xwesiyê nedikir.
 
And that mother-in-law only saw good things in that bride,
she never complained about that mother-in-law.

155
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:34,000
Di xwesiya me rabû, am ê rabûna. Em rabûn,
 
Our mother-in-law would wake up, we would wake up. We woke
up,

156
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:37,000
taştê kefa xwe çêkirin, em ez pez dotin,
 
we would make our breakfast, milk the sheep,

157
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:42,000
di êb e wexta me karê xwa hişt da rojê keran...
 
it was a shame at that time if we left our chores and the
sun hit us...

158
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:46,000
Taştê xwe ser da em ê da çûn palê.
 
We had our breakfast and we would go to do the harvest.

159
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:50,000
Heta şîvê am paleyî kirin am dihatin da mal.
 
Until night we would do the harvest and then come home.

160
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:54,000
Ê yên me ha, yên me ne yên xelkê.
 
For us... for us, not for other people.

161
00:11:54,000 --> 00:12:00,000
Em d'hatin mal, xwesiya ma mal, apê ma mal, tiştê me da
wan...
 
We would come home, our mother-in-law is at home, our
father-in-law is at home, they would give us things...

162
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:06,000
Bes didana me bixwera û am dihatina am di ketni rahet dibûni
me di xewa dikir.
 
If they just gave it, we would eat and we would come and
rest, we would sleep.

163
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:10,000
Da êşa û qîçên kûrik di nêv wan da, de êş...
 
The small pains of the boys among them... pains...

164
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:12,000
Hûn yê berê ji xew da saet çenda da radibûn?
 
You from the past, at what time did you wake up from sleep?

165
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:18,000
Ge t'yê berê saet çenda dibî... kî çê xwiçê ezan dida, em
hişyar dibûn.
 
What do you mean what time in the past... when the local
imam would give the call to prayer, we woke up.

166
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:22,000
Û heta ro dihêlin na. Û Xoca çi wext da ezan dida?
 
And until the sun rises. And what time did the imam give the
call to prayer?

167
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,000
Ber destê sibê.
 
In the early morning.

168
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:30,000
Erê, pêşiya ezan dida em radibûn. Ji piçûkê me heta nav
kalikê me.
 
Yes, before the call to prayer, we woke up. From the
smallest of us to the oldest of us.

169
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,000
Nabe ku mirov di te dît na heybeta wî wa ku civan e. Heftê
sal umir derbas kirine. Nabe rûyekî geş... cara rû b'ser xem
ketiye?
 
Well one sees you have the majesty of a young person. But
you have passed seventy years of life. How can your face be
so bright... did sadness ever fall upon your face?

170
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:34,000
Nabe ku me heftê sal umir derbas kirine nabe rûyekî geş.
 
How can we have passed seventy years of life... how could
there be a bright face.

171
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:37,000
Çawa ku rû bi ser xemê neketiye?
 
How could a face not have fallen into sorrow?

172
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:41,000
Carek rû b'ser xemê neketiye? Qet na, rû bi ser xeman
ketiye.
 
Has a face never fallen into sorrow? Absolutely not, the
face has fallen into sorrow.

173
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:46,000
Naxêr ez mebest dikim ew ji mastê de, vî çiqas mayî bi kelê?
 
No, I mean about the yogurt, how much of it has been
boiling?

174
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:52,000
Ew vallah wextî min datî ser agir, gava kela wê ket naha wê
saete digrim.
 
Well, when I put it on the fire, when it starts boiling, I
start timing it now.

175
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:58,000
Ez saetekê digrim du saet û çil daqîqe de, û an du saet û
nîva da êl ez mastê xwe dikelînim.
 
I time it, an hour, two hours and forty minutes, and in two
and a half hours, I will have boiled my yogurt.

176
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:00,000
De çiqasi mastê min baş bibe,
 
The better the yogurt,

177
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:03,000
qaymaxa wî der tê, zêr dibe rûyê mast, êdî ew mast e. Eger
deh salan jê re tiştek nabe.
 
its cream comes out, it becomes like gold on the surface of
the yogurt, then that is yogurt. Even for ten years, nothing
will happen to it.

178
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,000
Yanî gerek du saetan tu bikelînî?
 
So you have to boil it for two hours?

179
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:12,000
Erê eqelî di saetan da di çil deqeyan... di saetan... na qet
ez nizanim re îla ez bikelînim.
 
Yes, at least two hours, two hours and forty minutes... two
hours... I won't just let it boil like that.

180
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:14,000
Û dît ku te hev dida?
 
And did you see, you were stirring it?

181
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:18,000
Ewa nika tevlê nede, ê binî bigre.
 
Yes, otherwise it will catch, you have to stir it so the
bottom doesn't catch.

182
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:21,000
Ê baş e, em ê li wê derê vegerin bo te di karekî din da.
Xwedê ji te razî be.
 
Well, we will come back to you later for another task.
Thanks.

183
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:41,000
Spas ji te ra ji.
 
Thanks to you too.

184
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:50,000
Ev kengî çêkiriye, îsal in?
 
When was this made? This year?

185
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,000
Ê îsal e.
 
It's from this year.

186
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,000
Du sal in?
 
Is it two years old?

187
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:54,000
Yek sal e.
 
It is one year old.

188
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,000
Hûn niha derdixin dika qet xera nabe?
 
So you take these out, it doesn't get ruined?

189
00:13:56,000 --> 00:14:01,000
Na qet xerab nabe lê na.
 
No, it doesn't get ruined at all, no.

190
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:03,000
Yanî ew di çiqas wexte de maye çê nabe?
 
I mean, how much time can it stay without going bad?

191
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:13,000
Di wexta tu rind tevdidî, xwê rind dikî... tu dikarî dused
salî tu qefla wî bikî, tehl nabe. Lê wisa di cîye xwe de
dimîne.
 
When you stir it well, you salt it well... you can keep it
for two hundred years, you lock it, it won't go bitter. It
just stays in its place like that.

192
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:15,000
Yanî tu dibêjî ta dused salî tiştek nabe?
 
So you say that for two hundred years nothing happens to it?

193
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:18,000
Wisa di ciyê xwe de dimîne, nabe, deh salan qet nabe.
 
As long as it stays in its place like that, nothing happens,
for ten years absolutely nothing happens.

194
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:20,000
Hûn sibe êvarê çawa dixwin jê?
 
How do you eat it morning and evening?

195
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:32,000
Em tînin, dixin di sahana xwe de diînin, ev zeyta wî, dims û
tişt ew diînin sefreyê. Û germ hazer da dida te li sibehe.
 
We bring it, we put it in our plates, there is oil with it,
molasses, we put it on the table. It is ready and hot for
you in the morning.

196
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:35,000
Tikek nan dikî bin xwe tay tê didî û ti didî bi xwê r?
 
You take a piece of bread and eat it like that?

197
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:41,000
Xweş dibe. Nan dişkênî dixî dimsê, dixî zeytê, ti hez nakî
li ser sibehê wê tişta bixî.
 
It tastes good. You break the bread and dip it in molasses,
dip it in oil, you might not want to eat that thing in the
morning.

198
00:14:41,000 --> 00:15:00,000
Jinek ku dile wê hebe, radibe nepikek dikî ser sîra... belê
carke min mast sîra nekiriye. Hêlurkê dikim ewî nakim, min
qe bi wan tiştan hez nekiriye.
 
If a woman feels like it, she makes bread with garlic... yes
sometimes I put yogurt with garlic. I make spinach but I
don't do that, I don't eat those things.

199
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:02,000
Çima beriya sibehê ê te ewçend xweş e?
 
Why is yours so good before morning?

200
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:05,000
Qaymaxa ê xweş dibe.
 
Its cream gets very good.

201
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:06,000
Niha te dikarî karî xwe bikî?
 
Can you do your work now?

202
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:10,000
Kar jî loqa xwe ne mabe em pîr bûn.
 
The work has fallen out of my hands, we have gotten old.

203
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:18,000
Berê ez gelek karker bûm, tu kes l'gund ne dighaşti min, ez
wek we re bûm. Naha me we çaxê pir xebitî, min pîr bû.
 
I used to work a lot, no one in the village could keep up
with me, I would bring it here, now we have gotten old.

204
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:33,000
Mi sîr deçan.. baqdanos deçan... gêzer deçan... bacanê reş..
bacanê sor deçan.
 
I planted garlic, I planted parsley... I planted carrots...
I planted black eggplants... I planted red eggplants.

205
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:45,000
Yanî min qol dida.. ez diçuma nav çolê bi fasulya de.. ax
xwe de me da wek min pir di kir..
 
I mean I worked really hard... I would go to the field to
plant beans... I would dig the soil like that, I did a lot.

206
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:54,000
Ti bixî xelkî pirs bikî, ew de ti gûtin wilo ye. Îsal mi ew
berdan.
 
If you ask the people they will tell you it's like that.
This year I stopped.

207
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:58,000
Nika çi bikim? Niha di bikim, na kar nakim...
 
What can I do now? What can I do... I don't work...

208
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:00,000
Ê baş ev e.
 
This is good.

209
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,000
Vaye li min.
 
Yes, it is.

210
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:04,000
Te nebe lê, de bajêr rûne.
 
You shouldn't go to the city.

211
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:06,000
Xwedê ji te razi be, saeta te xweş be.
 
May God bless you, thanks for your time.

212
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:22,000
Saeta we ji xweş be.
 
Thanks to you too.

213
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:25,000
Gundê Omo li ser girekî bi navê Çinarê ava ye.
 
Omo village is built on a hill named Cinarê.

214
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:28,000
L'başûrê gund li ser riya Efrîn û Raco dikeve,
 
South of the village lies on the road between Afrin and
Rajo,

215
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:32,000
piştî gundê Qoqanê hatîye avakirin.
 
it was built after the village of Qoqan.

216
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:35,000
Gundê Omo girêdayî navçeya Mabeta ya Kantona Efrînê ye.
 
Omo village belongs to the Mabeta district of the Afrin
Canton.

217
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:38,000
Heft kîlometreyan li rohilatê bajarokê Mabeta,
 
It is seven kilometers east of the Mabeta town,

218
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:42,000
û deh kîlometreyan li bakurê bajarê Efrînê dikeve.
 
and ten kilometers north of the city of Afrin.

219
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:45,000
Navê gundê Omo ji malbata Omo hatiye,
 
The name of Omo village comes from the Omo family,

220
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:48,000
ku ew wekî damezrînerên gund têne naskirin.
 
as they are recognized as the founders of the village.

221
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,000
Ku ew ji eşîra Koçera bûn.
 
They were from the Kocher tribe.

222
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:53,000
Piştî wê malbata Sîno ji gundê Gulîka hatin,
 
After that, the Sino family came from Gulika village,

223
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:56,000
û gund bi hev re şên kirin.
 
and populated the village together.

224
00:16:56,000 --> 00:17:01,000
Tê gotin ku gund di sala hezar û heftsed û pêncî û diyan da
hatîye ava kirin.
 
It is said that the village was built in the year 1752.

225
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:20,000
Hêjayî bîrxistinê ye ku gundê Omo bi navê Înhacerê jî tê nas
kirin.
 
It is worth mentioning that Omo village is also known as
Enhajera.

226
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:25,000
Belê iro em li gundê Omo ne, me xwest xweşîyên vî gundî
bêtir nas bikin.
 
Yes, today we are in Omo village, we wanted to know the
beauties of this village better.

227
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:30,000
Lê dema ku ji gund dertên... em bi du kîlometreyan dertên...
di nav diravê dara de...
 
But when you leave the village... for two kilometers... we
go... between the path of the trees...

228
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,000
Me berê xwe da wê avê zîrav kê.
 
We headed towards that thin river.

229
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:35,000
Hindek dibêjin ava Cûmê ye, hindek dibêjin ava zîrav kê ye.
 
Some say it's the water of Cume, some say it's the water of
Zirav.

230
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:39,000
Lê derbarî wekî rû bi rû me pîçek dît, me meraq kir.
 
But regarding the face to face, we saw a bit, we became
curious.

231
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:42,000
Me xwest ku em dîroka wê aşê jî em nas bikin.
 
We wanted to know the history of that mill as well.

232
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:45,000
Kê d'vî gundî jî darbas bûn, em spasîya wan de kin.
 
Whoever passed through this village, we thank them.

233
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:48,000
Lê em ê bipirsin dîroka wê aşê...
 
But we will ask about the history of that mill...

234
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,000
Merheba ji we re.
 
Hello to you.

235
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,000
Ehlen we sehlen...
 
Welcome...

236
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:52,000
Em di te nas bikin, destpêkê?
 
Can we get to know you, to begin with?

237
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,000
Em Zilma Hisê Reşo ne...
 
I am Zilma Hise Resho...

238
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:54,000
Ser çavê me apê Zilma.
 
On my eyes uncle Zilma.

239
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:56,000
Aşek l'vir habû?
 
Was there a mill here?

240
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:57,000
Evo ye.
 
There is.

241
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,000
Lê min aş nedî l'vir.
 
But I didn't see a mill here.

242
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:00,000
Aş tûne bu xerobî gî naş tû.
 
There is no mill, it got destroyed...

243
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:02,000
Kevnare a vî devrê...
 
An ancient one in this area...

244
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:05,000
Kevrên wî hene ev jî d'hatin aşa Hanîm Bozo.
 
Its stones are here, they used to come to Hanim Bozo mill.

245
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,000
Kaniyên aşê l'ber hebûn.
 
The springs of the mill were in front of it.

246
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:11,000
Gundê Ên Hacer, Gundê Koka... gîş dahatin l'ser wê robariya
vî we dîk.
 
The village of En Hacer, the village of Koka... they all
came on this river and saw it.

247
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:13,000
Berî gıştî d'hatin ser wê aşê.
 
Previously everyone would come to that mill.

248
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:15,000
Di wextê em me ew didît e, eqîk piçûk bûn.
 
At the time when we saw it, we were very small.

249
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:20,000
Em da hatin wî aşî, xelk gî d'hatina vê aşî da.
 
We came to that mill, all the people came to this mill.

250
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:27,000
Mesele erabaneyê wan durna diketin, dîsa kiç d'çûn mal sibe
roj d'hatin wira.
 
For example, if it wasn't their cart's turn, they would go
back home and come back there the next day.

251
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:30,000
E wê aşa navê wê Hanîm Bûzû yê dî sar bî e gotin ê d'bêjin
aşê Hanîm Bûzû.
 
The name of that mill was Hanim Bozo, they called it the
Hanim Bozo mill.

252
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:33,000
Wî ew tenê bû lê kasîk dî bû?
 
Was it just that one or was there someone else?

253
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:34,000
Ortaxê xwe l'vê hev bûn.
 
They had partners here together.

254
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,000
Kî bûn?
 
Who were they?

255
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:37,000
Ortaxê xwe d'vê Emerî Şêxkî bûn.
 
The partners were from the Emeri Shexki family.

256
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,000
Ji Gundî Ên Hecerê bûn.
 
They were from the village of En Hecere.

257
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:43,000
L'Gundê Ên Hecer bûn u Omerî Şêx bûn paşê de hatin l'vê.
 
They were from the village of En Hecer and were Omer Shex,
then they came here.

258
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,000
Û wî çaxî l'vê der ê ev aş e...
 
And at that time here this mill...

259
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:46,000
Û ew çend gund dihatin l'ser wî aşê?
 
And how many villages came to this mill?

260
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:49,000
Di heft heşt gund d'hatin. Amara di hatin...
 
Seven or eight villages came. Amara came...

261
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:58,000
Şêxwûtka dahatin, pîşya aşî l'vê d'ketna koka rûbarî dahat
in... Gundê... heta di ketin tîna am di wira dahatin vî aşî
tî ni bûn l'vê derê..
 
Shekhutka came... below the mill they fell in the river
path... The village... until they entered they came to this
mill, there were none others in this area here..

262
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:03,000
Piştre av aşî wî gundî ê Hasen Sêd da ser rûbar l'wê l'pîşa
wî am gund vî aşî şolî d'kir.
 
Then after the mill of that village, Hasan Sed was built on
the river... in front of it, this mill worked for the
village.

263
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:07,000
Ew gund aş li vî pêş we di av li ser wê avê dişixulî kar
dikir.
 
That village mill was here in front and worked on that
water.

264
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:10,000
E, berê wê li ser vê avê dişixulî.
 
Yes, it used to work on this water.

265
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:13,000
Wî yê kengî wî aş hebû?
 
Since when was that mill there?

266
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:23,000
Aş cangê bû nizanime, a di sîn me.. a ş gî ewa ez piçûk da
bûn... mesel e wî di hat ne ê çî a di ew gşta d'çûn Heleb
d'meza ê aş xirab û...
 
Since when the mill was there, I don't know exactly... I was
small... until for example they would go to do the harvest
and go to Aleppo, then the mill was ruined...

267
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:27,000
Yanî paştî wî ko milet fêr bûn, çûn Heleb ev aş xera bûn.
 
So after people went to Aleppo, this mill was ruined.

268
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:30,000
Erê, o di paşi wê.
 
Yes, and after that.

269
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:33,000
Paşê a d'ket mator av l'nîv am d'hatin ser mator, a m ro aş
xera bû.
 
Then the motor mills came, we went to the motor... these
water mills were ruined.

270
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:37,000
A de paştê mator da r e ketna ê wê r aş di a xira bûn.
 
Yes, after the motors came out that mill broke down.

271
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:39,000
Gihêşte te ku wî da kar ki?
 
Did you get to work in it?

272
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:46,000
Gîhaşti me. Am bi xwada d'hatin wî aşê me beşa xwe da tî
d'hêran.
 
Yes, I reached it. We used to come here ourselves and bring
our portion to grind.

273
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:51,000
Dema dixebitîn ew kî bûn, kesên kar dikirin hevkarê we kî
bûn?
 
When they were working, who were they, who were the people
working, your partners?

274
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:56,000
Yê ku dekar kir Xalê Bûzû Mûsa l'wê... l'der aş bû.
 
The one who worked was Uncle Bozo Musa there... by the mill.

275
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:58,000
Ev ciq qasa xwe çend kes di aş de dixebitîn l'vê?
 
So how many people worked in this mill?

276
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:00,000
Du mêran.
 
Two men.

277
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:04,000
Tê bîra te di dema xirabiyê, yanî li te tişt ji Helebê, yan
deverên din dihatin?
 
Do you remember during the times of crisis, did anything
come from Aleppo or other places?

278
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,000
Hmm?
 
Hmm?

279
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:07,000
Tê bîra te di dema xirabiyê de, yanî êrîş li ser Helebê û
deverên din çêdibûn?
 
Do you remember during the times of crisis, meaning when
attacks were happening in Aleppo and other places?

280
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:11,000
Welle Helebî jî... Beriya şoreşê, Helebî nedihatin.
 
Well, people from Aleppo... Before the revolution, the
people of Aleppo wouldn't come.

281
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:15,000
Çu xirabî nebûn. Lê min zanîbû, xelkê di got aşê Ziravkê
xirab bûn.
 
There was no destruction. But I knew, the people used to say
the Ziravk mill was destroyed.

282
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:18,000
Ava wê nema bû, av xirab bûbû.
 
Its water had stopped, the water became ruined.

283
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:20,000
Apê min, em te jî...
 
Uncle, let's...

284
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,000
Em te jî nas bikin.
 
Let's get to know you as well.

285
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:24,000
Ehlen û sehlen bi hatina we.
 
Welcome, it's good to have you here.

286
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,000
Ser çavan.
 
Thank you.

287
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:25,000
Em te nas bikin?
 
May you be healthy.

288
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,000
Em te nas bikin?
 
Can we get to know you?

289
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:28,000
Ez Cemal im, kurê Osmanê Hecî me.
 
I am Cemal, the son of Osman Heci.

290
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:29,000
Ser çava me.
 
You are welcome.

291
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,000
Ti sax bî.
 
May you be healthy.

292
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:33,000
Birêz Cemal... niha em qala aşan bikin.
 
Mr. Cemal... now let's talk about the mills.

293
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:37,000
Te dît li çiyayê Kurmênc, li Efrînê gelek aş hebûn.
 
You've seen that in the Kurd Mountains, in Afrin, there were
many mills.

294
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:41,000
Niha em behsa kîjan deverê bikin, li kû derê av hebû aş jî
li wê derê hebû, ne wisa ye?
 
Now, whichever region we talk about, wherever there was
water, there was a mill there too, isn't that right?

295
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:43,000
Doxrî ye.
 
That's right.

296
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:46,000
Naxwe em behsa aşan bikin, aşek tenê li vir hebû yan aşên
din jî li vir hebûn?
 
So let's talk about the mills, was there only one mill here
or were there other mills here too?

297
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:48,000
Welle, dibêjin Aşê Ziravkê...
 
Well, they say the Ziravk Mill...

298
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:52,000
Dibe aşekî din jî li jêr hebe. Em negihiştinê, yanî min
nedîtiye.
 
There might be another mill further down. We didn't catch
its time, I haven't seen it.

299
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:52,000
Ez nedîme, na.
 
You haven't seen it?

300
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:54,000
Ez nedîme, na.
 
I haven't seen it, no.

301
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:57,000
Bes ew aşo, bav û kalê min bi wî de xebitîne.
 
But this mill, my father and grandfather worked in it.

302
00:20:57,000 --> 00:21:00,000
Kalê min navê wî Henan, bavkê min jî navê xwî Osman bû.
 
My grandfather's name was Henan, and my father's name was
Osman.

303
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:02,000
Ew di vî aşî de xebitîne.
 
They worked in this mill.

304
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:03,000
Tê bîra te?
 
Do you remember?

305
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:06,000
Na, nayê bîra min, na... Di dû min de..
 
No, I don't remember, no... It was after me..

306
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:08,000
Yanî.. berî min bû.
 
Meaning.. it was before my time.

307
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:11,000
Û herq ji vê avê re dirêj dibû, herq ji binê zinar dihat.
 
And a stream would extend from this water, the stream would
come from under the rock.

308
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:14,000
Bi herqê ve, dihat.. dihat ta di vê dere,
 
Through the stream, it would flow... it would flow until
this place,

309
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:18,000
Û herq jî ava diweda de, diderdikirin.. ta dibinîya zinar
de.
 
And the stream would return the water, and they would
extract it... until beneath the rock.

310
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:20,000
Û xelkê tînan, arvanê xwu tînan..
 
And the people would bring their flour, they would bring
it..

311
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:23,000
Li der dihêran û tînan, tiştên wisa dikirin radikirin û ard
dixwarin.
 
Here they ground it and brought it, they would do such
things and eat the flour.

312
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:26,000
Heta niha jî aş hin hene li Efrînê,
 
Even today, there are some mills in Afrin,

313
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:28,000
Wek nimûne em dibînin li gundê Mara tî heye,
 
As an example, we see there's one in the village of Mara,

314
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:29,000
Li gundê Bablûrê heye.
 
There is one in the village of Bablur.

315
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:30,000
Û gelek aşên din jî hene.
 
And there are many other mills too.

316
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:34,000
Yanî, di dema şoreşê de tê dît ew dema riyên derdora Efrînê
gişta teqîya qut kirin, rê qut bûn.
 
I mean, during the revolution, you see when all the roads
around Afrin were exploded and cut off, the roads were
closed.

317
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:35,000
Hmm.
 
Hmm.

318
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:36,000
Hêsir li ser Efrînê çêbû...
 
A blockade happened on Afrin...

319
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:38,000
Lê dîsa ew aşan ha vegeriyan.
 
But those mills became operational again.

320
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,000
Vegerîn..
 
They returned..

321
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,000
Yanî eger ev aş jî saxlem ba..
 
Meaning if this mill was intact as well..

322
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,000
naha wacib ew jî wek carekî kar bikira, na?
 
it would probably be working again now, wouldn't it?

323
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,000
Doxrî ye.
 
That's right.

324
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:44,000
Erê..
 
Yes..

325
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,000
Naxwe em te jî nas bikin?
 
Then let's get to know you too?

326
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:45,000
Ti sax bî.
 
Welcome..

327
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:46,000
Ti sax bî.
 
May you be healthy.

328
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:50,000
Ti sax bî, navê min Mihemed e, lawê Şêxo Sîno me. Ji gundê
Omo me.
 
May you be healthy, my name is Mihemed, I am the son of Sexo
Sino. I am from the village of Omo.

329
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,000
Ser çava.
 
Thank you.

330
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,000
Ji malbata Sîno me, ewa.
 
I am from the Sino family, exactly.

331
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:55,000
Naxwe em behsa... milet tê vir rûdinê li vir, nê?
 
Let's talk about... the people come and sit here, right?

332
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:57,000
Ehlen û sehlen. Ev der.. minteqek pir xweş e,
 
Welcome. Here.. is a very beautiful area,

333
00:21:57,000 --> 00:22:00,000
rûniştina milete. Kêf dikin, nonî xwu tînin..
 
it's a place for people to sit. They enjoy themselves, they
bring their bread..

334
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:02,000
xwe xwarinê xwe tînin. Av jî heye.
 
they bring their food. There's water too.

335
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:05,000
Xwu rûdiniştin li bin vê dara de.. sî ye, wedahesin..
 
They sit under this tree.. there's shade, they rest..

336
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:08,000
Ev milet da.. pir xweş e. Minteqek pir xweş e.
 
These people.. it's very nice. It is a very beautiful area.

337
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,000
Yanî, ev der cihê geştyaran e?
 
So, this is a place for tourists?

338
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:11,000
Erê, cihê rûniştinê ye.
 
Yes, it is a place for sitting.

339
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,000
Cihê merî wenda dihesînê..
 
A place where people can rest..

340
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:16,000
Cihê merî mirtah dibe ye, piran.. pir diçûn dirûştin
dıdîtin. Pir xweş e. Çi bêjim te?
 
A place where people find comfort, many.. many would go sit
and see. It is very beautiful. What can I tell you?

341
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,000
Pir xweş e, yane.
 
It's very nice, I mean.

342
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:20,000
We te dîtî milet jî tên.. makîneyê xwu tînin.
 
You see the people come too.. they bring their cars.

343
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:22,000
Li bin darê xwuda rudinin, av jî heye.
 
They sit under their trees, there's water too.

344
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:24,000
Xwu qirçekî av didin, zarê xwu didine avê.
 
They splash some water, they let their children play in the
water.

345
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,000
Û wexta jî av pir dibî,
 
And back when there used to be a lot of water,

346
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:27,000
Lê berî.. ev çar-pênc sal.
 
But before.. it has been four or five years.

347
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:29,000
Bi çar-pênc sal e.. baran tine ye.. av noka kêm bûye.
 
For four or five years.. there has been no rain.. the water
has decreased now.

348
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:31,000
Lê berî.. masî ji tê hebin..
 
But before.. there used to be fish too..

349
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:32,000
Me masiyên ji tê de digirtin..
 
We would catch fish from it too..

350
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:35,000
Û milet jî xwe tînin.. li ber vê avê xwu tê de digerîn,
yane.
 
And people come too.. they wander around the water.

351
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:36,000
Pir xweş e, yane.
 
It's very nice, you see.

352
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:38,000
Yanî berî av jî li vê derê gî... pir bû?
 
So before, the water here was... plentiful?

353
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:40,000
Pirr bû, pirr. Di tewrê xwe de wê bibe. Di panzdeh sal an
zêdetir we hebû.
 
It was a lot, a lot. It was naturally like that. It was like
that for fifteen years or more.

354
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:44,000
Baran hin dikir, av niha tine yane, av kêm e yanî.
 
Rain fell a bit, there's no water now, water is scarce.

355
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:46,000
Bes berê av pirr bû.. pirr pirr.. pirr bû yane.
 
But before, there was a lot of water.. a lot.. there was a
lot.

356
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:49,000
Yanî ev aşo.. aş ser awê dişixulî yane.
 
So this mill.. the mill worked by water power.

357
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:54,000
Izer av ne pirr ba, nedişixulî yane.
 
If there wasn't a lot of water, it wouldn't work.

358
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:59,000
Û nîv kîlometro, bin zinar ji herqê ra dadihat, da herê,
dadihat ser aş yane.
 
And for half a kilometer, a stream came from under the rock,
to go, it came onto the mill.

359
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:02,000
Bes berî çend sal baran nîne, û av jî kêm bûyî...
 
But for the past few years there has been no rain, and the
water has decreased...

360
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:06,000
Îde dîsa wek dîsa milet... gundek ji milete... yex milet ji
mintiqê te û li dera xwu rûdinişin dixwin.
 
But still people... people from a village... like people
from the region come and sit down here and eat.

361
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:08,000
Digerrin, xwu da kêf dikin..
 
They stroll around, they enjoy themselves..

362
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:09,000
Bes hîşîneyê jî heye..
 
But there's also greenery..

363
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:12,000
Li ber avê jî, hin tiyek der tûzek jî dibê..
 
By the water, sometimes some watercress grows..

364
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:14,000
Mendik jî dibe.. tiştên wiha hebin.
 
Mendik (wild edible herb) grows too.. there are such things.

365
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:18,000
Masiyên jî tê hebin.. Pir xweş e.. yanî pir gelek xweş e vir
dere, yane...
 
There would be fishes too.. It's very nice.. meaning this
place is very very nice...

366
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:19,000
Apê Cemal...
 
Uncle Cemal...

367
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:19,000
Apê Remzî..
 
Yes?

368
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:20,000
Apê Remzî..
 
Uncle Remzi..

369
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:21,000
Hmm.
 
Hmm.

370
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:24,000
Naha ev li vî derî, ew li çend kaniyên hene? Kanî.
 
Now around this place, how many springs are there? Springs.

371
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:28,000
Me gote Ziravkê hebû... Lê qeydî wê çi kanî hene... çend
kanî li vir hene?
 
We said there was Ziravk... But besides that, what springs
are there... how many springs are here?

372
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,000
Kaniya Êşê heye,
 
There's the Eshe Spring,

373
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:31,000
Kaniya Kokanê heye,
 
There's the Kokane Spring,

374
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:34,000
Û dîsa Kaniya Bikê heye.
 
And there is the Bike Spring.

375
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:36,000
Ev kanîne li vir hene.
 
These are the springs around here.

376
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,000
Sê kanî nîn in?
 
Are there not three springs?

377
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:37,000
Û ew her sê kanî, navê te hene?
 
Hmm.

378
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:39,000
Û ew her sê kanî, navê te hene?
 
And do you have names for all three springs?

379
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:41,000
La welle av tê heye lê...
 
Well, there is water in them...

380
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:46,000
Êdî tê ava min jî ew kanîne.. Kaniya Kokanê, Kaniya Bikê...
Kaniya Êşê.. Kaniya Êşê dere jêr e.
 
And the water to me is those springs.. Kokane Spring, Bike
Spring... Eshe Spring.. Eshe Spring flows downwards.

381
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:48,000
Avên din di kû derê tên?
 
Where do the other waters come from?

382
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:49,000
Avê din,
 
The other water,

383
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:51,000
ro... ro..
 
It... it..

384
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:54,000
Ji enwerê tirkiyê av dida wî.. ew der tê..
 
The water flows from the Turkish side.. that place.

385
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:59,000
Gelek hebin te.. av tinebe.. av tine yanî..
 
If there is a lot, it flows.. if there is no water.. there
is no water, you see..

386
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:01,000
Ez tiştek din ji te pirs dikim,
 
I'll ask you something else,

387
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:03,000
Naha tê dibêjî "Zinarê Îniyê."
 
You mention "Zinare Iniye" (The Friday Rock).

388
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:04,000
Ewa.
 
Yes.

389
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:06,000
Çima gote dibêjin Zinarê Îniyê li vir?
 
Why did they say it's called Zinare Iniye here?

390
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:08,000
Welle...
 
Well...

391
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:11,000
Dibêjin Zinarê Îniyê, yane mehaneyê ev gund e..
 
They call it Zinare Iniye, the meaning of this village..

392
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:14,000
Ew yên mazın beriya me de gund digotin.. me digo, xêr e
dibêjin Zinarê Îniyê?
 
The older people before us in the village used to say.. we
asked, why is it called Zinare Iniye?

393
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:15,000
Wan di go..
 
They would say..

394
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:17,000
Ruyê îniyê.. hebarek inî bi qebrek kî..
 
On a Friday.. a spirit/jinni was trapped..

395
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:22,000
ji Herwiye kevirê şeyda.. inî dîtin ew kevirê şeyda dê kavil
be...
 
Every time a crazy rock fell.. they believed a Friday spirit
was crushed by the rock...

396
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:25,000
Îna çiqa dev gundiyan em tiştê dî.. nav hene.
 
There are so many names for the villages and other things.

397
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:26,000
Em nizanin ev bi rast e an na in..
 
We don't know if this is true or not.

398
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:28,000
Welle her de..
 
Well, in any case..

399
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:29,000
Şikefte.. Şikefte jî dev li vê gund hene?
 
Caves.. are there any caves around this village?

400
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:30,000
Han şikeft heye.
 
There is a cave.

401
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:31,000
Çend şikefte in?
 
How many caves are there?

402
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:32,000
Du du ne.
 
There are two.

403
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:33,000
Navên xwu çend.. an we wisa nin?
 
Do they have any names.. or are they just like that?

404
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:35,000
Dibên Şikeftê Zinarê Îniyê..
 
They call it the Zinare Iniye Cave.

405
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:36,000
Ey bi navê wiya şikefta zinarê Îniyê..
 
Oh, it goes by the name of Zinare Iniye Cave..

406
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:37,000
Her wisa..
 
Just like that..

407
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,000
Erê
 
Yes

408
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:40,000
Şikefta zinarê Îniyê..
 
Zinare Iniye Cave..

409
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:42,000
Tê bîra min, Zinarê lı wî derê ha..
 
I remember, under the rock there..

410
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:47,000
li wê derê dibê, zinarê.. qicikek.. a çûçek qicik mi nedî
diderbas bikin..
 
there, there's a rock.. a small.. a small hole I haven't
seen that they pass through..

411
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:50,000
Ew qicikên.. deha hêsan rihet dibin.
 
