00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:39,000
Ee malbatên malên Sîno ji Gulîko hatin.
 
Ee families of Sino's houses came from Guliko.

546
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:44,000
Ee malbatên malên Bozo, ji Alciya hatin.
 
Ee families of Bozo's houses, came from Alciya.

547
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:50,000
Ee malbatên malên Silo... ji memşemik hatin.
 
Ee families of Silo's houses... came from Memshemik.

548
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:57,000
Ee malbatên malên Delo ji Wanê hatin... malbatên malên
Hemdê, ew jî ji Sicê hatin.
 
Ee families of Delo's houses came from Wan... families of
Hemde's houses, they also came from Sice.

549
00:33:57,000 --> 00:34:00,000
Sicê hatin... ew jî hatin li gund rûniştin.
 
Came from Sice... they also came and settled in the village.

550
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:04,000
Gî bi hev re ra ... dijîn.
 
We all live together.

551
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:08,000
Na, te behsa ... pênc malbata kir, ba va dibin şeş?
 
Now, you mentioned... five families, with this they become
six?

552
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:12,000
Em va dibin şeş, erê. Şeş malbat di gundê me da hene. Gundê
Omo da hene.
 
With us they become six, yes. There are six families in our
village. In the village of Omo.

553
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:12,000
Şeş malbat hene û ... me jin dan hevdu ... me jin dan hevdu
û em gişk... bi hev re re... danîşîn.
 
Yes.

554
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:24,000
Şeş malbat hene û ... me jin dan hevdu ... me jin dan hevdu
û em gişk... bi hev re re... danîşîn.
 
There are six families and... we intermarried... we
intermarried and we all... settled together.

555
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:26,000
Apê Henîf, em bi xwe ji kîjan eşîrê ne?
 
Uncle Henif, which tribe are we from ourselves?

556
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:30,000
Em ji eşîra ... Koçerên Delikî ne.
 
We are from the tribe... of Deliki Nomads.

557
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:31,000
Hun bi xwe giştî koçer in?
 
Are you all nomads yourselves?

558
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:35,000
Em... giştî koçer in.
 
We... are all nomads.

559
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:37,000
E na... gundê we çiqas xanî tê de heye?
 
E now... how many houses are there in your village?

560
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:43,000
Ee... 60-70 mal... 80 mal... tê de heye.
 
Ee... 60-70 houses... 80 houses... are in it.

561
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:44,000
Him...
 
Hmm...

562
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:47,000
60-70 mal... tê de heye.
 
60-70 houses... are in it.

563
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:50,000
Wek debara jiyana xwe hûn debara xwe bi çi dikin?
 
How do you make your livelihood for your life?

564
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:53,000
Em debara xwe bi ... berê ... berê pez bû.
 
We make our livelihood with... in the past... in the past it
was sheep.

565
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:55,000
Berê pez bû.
 
In the past it was sheep.

566
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:57,000
Pez... çû...
 
Sheep... went...

567
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:59,000
Hinda bû...
 
Disappeared...

568
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:10,000
Debara xwe ... me zeytûn çandin... me erd kirê yan me erd...
em diçînin... genimê xwe cihê xwe diçînin... nîskên xwe,
nokên xwe... em gişt tiştî diçînin.
 
Our livelihood... we planted olives... we rented land or we
land... we plant... we plant our wheat, our barley... our
lentils, our chickpeas... we plant everything.

569
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:19,000
Û zeytûnê me ... mewsim tê em zeytûnê xwe ra dikin... zeyta
xwe... hiltînin, têra xwe hiltînin ê zêde jî em difiroşin.
 
And our olives... the season comes we pick our olives... our
oil... we keep, we keep enough for ourselves and the extra
we sell.

570
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:22,000
Û em giştik ... bi hev re ra ... diheşin.
 
And we all... live together mixed.

571
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:29,000
Gî... wekî xwişk û bira kî gî... wekî... kanê malek e.
 
All... like sisters and brothers all... like... it's like
one house.

572
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:40,000
Nuko... mamel e, nuko... zarokên we mezin dibin, diherin ...
mekteba, dixwînin,
 
Now... dealings, now... your children grow up, they go to...
schools, they study,

573
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:58,000
Mamosteyên jî derdikevin... ee... ee... keçkên me jî der in,
werşe jî li cem me hene... werşeyên dirûtinê jî hene...
werşeyên xeyatê jî hene... metbe'e sûretan jî hene... der in
dişuxilin... ew jî... cem me li gund hene.
 
Teachers also graduate... ee... ee... our girls also go, we
also have workshops... we also have sewing workshops... we
also have tailoring workshops... we also have photo
printing... they go and work... those too... are with us in
the village.

574
00:35:58,000 --> 00:36:03,000
Na berê şoreşê da, gelek milet... ji gund derketibû?
 
Now before the revolution, did a lot of people... leave the
village?

575
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:04,000
Gundê me jî derketibûn?
 
Did they leave our village too?

576
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:05,000
Wellehî derketin.
 
By God they left.

577
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:11,000
Derketin... hinek çûn Efrînê, hinek çûn Helebê... de hinek
jî çûn...
 
They left... some went to Efrin, some went to Aleppo... and
some also went...

578
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:14,000
Her hinek çûn welatê derve...
 
Some went to foreign countries...

579
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:19,000
L' pey meîşeta xwe digerin.
 
They are looking for their livelihood.

580
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:22,000
Na em bêjin ... Apê Henîf, berê rûspî wekî kî bûn di gund
da?
 
Now let's say... Uncle Henif, in the past who were the
elders in the village?

581
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:42,000
Rûspiyê me îşte ee... ku te ra bêjim... rûspiyê me ...
Îbrahîm hebû, Emerê ... Hesen hebu, de ... Xelîl hebû,
Mehemedê Sîno hebû... Bafkê min Mistefa hebû... Henanê Bozo
hebû...
 
Our elders well ee... if I tell you... our elders... there
was Ibrahim, there was Emere ... Hesen, then... there was
Xelil, there was Mehemede Sino... my grandfather Mistefa was
there... there was Henane Bozo...

582
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:46,000
Gellek rûspî hebûn.
 
There were many elders.

583
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:50,000
Henanê ... Silo hebû... evna giştik hebûn.
 
There was Henane... Silo... they were all there.

584
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:51,000
Spasiya te dikim.
 
I thank you.

585
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:52,000
Ser çava.
 
On the eyes.

586
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:53,000
Saet a te xweş.
 
May your time be pleasant.

587
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:55,000
Ser çava.
 
On the eyes.

588
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:56,000
Ser çava.
 
On the eyes.

589
00:36:56,000 --> 00:37:00,000
Ser çava... û hatina we... ser çavê me.
 
On the eyes... and your coming... on our eyes.

590
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:12,000
Sax bî saet a te xweş, Apê Henîf.
 
Be healthy, may your hours be pleasant, Uncle Henif.

591
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:22,000
Rûspiyên gund, Henan Omo, Sîno Kulîk, Mihemed Sîno, Îbrahîm
Reşo ku bi navê dengbêj Şikdar nas dikin, û Şêxê Xwesîno
hene.
 
The elders of the village, Henan Omo, Sino Kulik, Mihemed
Sino, Ibrahim Resho who is known by the name of the singer
Shikdar, and Sheikh Xwesino.

592
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:27,000
Cemîl Dalo karê... cebirandina dest û lingên şikestî dike.
 
Cemil Dalo does the work... of setting broken hands and
legs.

593
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:40,000
Her wiha rêjeya xwendinê jî di gund de... gellekî baş e.
Nêzî bîst kesan zanîngeh di beşên cure bi cure de qedandine.
 
Also the rate of education in the village... is very good.
About twenty people have finished university in various
departments.

594
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:41,000
Merheba stêran.
 
Hello viewers.

595
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:43,000
Ehlen... hatin ser serê me û ser çavê me ... û axa welat.
 
Welcome... you came on our head and on our eyes... and the
land of the homeland.

596
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:45,000
Sax bî... çavê te neêşin.
 
Be healthy... may your eyes not hurt.

597
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:47,000
Apê can em te nas bikin destpêkê?
 
Dear Uncle, let us know you first?

598
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:50,000
Navê min Hanan Xelîl Reşo ye.
 
My name is Hanan Xelil Resho.

599
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:55,000
Apê Hanan... ev karê dermanan te ji kê girt... kê pêşî te
çêkir... di malbata te de kes hebu dermanan çêdikir?
 
Uncle Hanan... from whom did you get this medicine work...
who made it before you... was there anyone in your family
making medicines?

600
00:37:55,000 --> 00:37:58,000
Na ew tişt tinebû. Ji gundê Hec Xelîl.
 
No that thing didn't exist. From the village of Hec Xelil.

601
00:37:58,000 --> 00:38:00,000
Cemîl Menan Reşîd
 
Cemil Menan Rashid

602
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:01,000
Pirtûkekê wî hebû...
 
He had a book...

603
00:38:01,000 --> 00:38:02,000
Yanî we ji pirtûkê girtiye?
 
I mean you got it from a book?

604
00:38:02,000 --> 00:38:06,000
Erê me ji pirtûkê girtiye... û em çêdikin amade dixwînin...
 
Yes we got it from a book... and we make it ready we read...

605
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:14,000
Ev çewîr e... e çi nexweşî ye... giya kom diki am ji wi re
vê çewîre çêdikin û pê didin
 
This is medicine... whatever disease there is... we gather
herbs we make this medicine for it and give it to it.

606
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:15,000
Kê nivîsandî pirtûk?
 
Who wrote the book?

607
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:20,000
Pirtûk... Doktorekî Yewnanî navê xwe Bost e.
 
Book... A Greek doctor whose name is Bost.

608
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:24,000
Tîmsala wî heta niha li saheha Atîna ye.
 
His statue is still in the square of Athens.

609
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:25,000
Li Yûnanê.
 
In Greece.

610
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:26,000
Wî nivîsandî?
 
He wrote it?

611
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:28,000
Wî nivîsandî tarcuma li Lûbnanê kirine.
 
He wrote it, they translated it in Lebanon.

612
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:30,000
E vegerandina erebî?
 
E translation to Arabic?

613
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:34,000
Vegerandina erebî ye zimanê erebî...
 
Translation to Arabic, Arabic language...

614
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:36,000
Û tê de heye... bi navê kurmancî.
 
And it's in there... with the Kurmanji name.

615
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:37,000
Wekî çi ye nanê?
 
Like what for example?

616
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:40,000
Wek deziya werdî...
 
Like standard thread...

617
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:42,000
Wek... berdî...
 
Like... bardi...

618
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:45,000
Bêriyê avê am dibin Berdî
 
By the water we say Bardi

619
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:52,000
Ewna dibin kirfes... yanî seqa em dibin qernebî
 
They say celery... meaning seqa we say cauliflower

620
00:38:52,000 --> 00:39:00,000
Yanî gelek tişt... tê da hene... nêzîkî hev in û kurmancî tê
heye.
 
I mean there are many things in it... they are close to each
other and there is Kurmanji in it.

621
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:03,000
Na Apê Hanan, çend sal e tu derman çêdikî?
 
Now Uncle Hanan, for how many years have you been making
medicine?

622
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:05,000
Deh, dozdeh sal in e.
 
It's been ten, twelve years.

623
00:39:05,000 --> 00:39:09,000
Yanî deh sal yazdeh sal ti vî karî dikî.
 
I mean for ten years, eleven years you've been doing these
works.

624
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:09,000
Te dermanî çî çêdikir?
 
Yes...

625
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:10,000
Te dermanî çî çêdikir?
 
What medicines did you make?

626
00:39:10,000 --> 00:39:16,000
Dermanî... her yekî nexweşiya xwa çi be... ev yêrê ji me ra
xeber de, ezê jî herim, çewîra wî bikim,
 
Medicine... everyone whatever their illness is... he sends
us a message, and I will go, make his medicine,

627
00:39:16,000 --> 00:39:18,000
Û ber bi emilînim
 
And use it

628
00:39:18,000 --> 00:39:21,000
Duxwazî eşyara çêkim duxwazî herra
 
If you want me to make things if you want me to go

629
00:39:21,000 --> 00:39:22,000
Heta hev dîna teva bikim.
 
Until I mix them all together.

630
00:39:22,000 --> 00:39:23,000
Bikelînim.
 
Boil it.

631
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:27,000
Yanî wek çiyane... heta nuke kes... hatine cem te ji bo çi
nexweşiyên te derman... derman çêkiriye ji bo çi nexweşî te
derman çêkiriye?
 
I mean like what... until now people... have come to you for
what illnesses have you medicine... made medicine for what
illness have you made medicine?

632
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:35,000
Ê di rûvî re hebe... em vê jê re derman çêdikin... û em
didinê... û her wextî ser de rehet dibe.
 
The one who has it in the intestines... we make medicine for
this... and we give it... and every time he gets comfortable
from it.

633
00:39:35,000 --> 00:39:37,000
Ê kevir wê re hebe...
 
The one who has stones...

634
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:38,000
Qûm wê re hebe...
 
The one who has sand...

635
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:44,000
Di gurçikên we da... Derbên em jê ra çêdikin... em didinê...
te herî bikelînî...
 
In your kidneys... The doses we make for them... we give
it... you go and boil it...

636
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:45,000
Tevef dikî...
 
You mix it...

637
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:49,000
Nîvî avê jê xelas be... û nîvî din tê dînî... tê vexiwî...
 
Half of its water gets finished... and the other half you
bring... you drink it...

638
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:51,000
Bi sivînê.
 
In the morning.

639
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:54,000
Da ew kevir wek şaşikî ra derbas kî, bi vê avê...
 
Then that stone you pass it like easily, with this water...

640
00:39:54,000 --> 00:40:00,000
Weha îşta ew tûrtîbê wê, ew gemara wê re nekeve nav.
 
Thus that is its arrangement, that dirt won't stay inside.

641
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:13,000
Kasa xwe ê xiriyê vaxwe, û nîvroj ê ya xwe vaxwe, û êvarê ê
ya xwe vaxwe, û qe werbe... qe quwîn be vêra nanîne.
 
Drink your final cup, and drink your noon cup, and drink
your evening cup, and if there is... if there is any
constipation, it will not happen.

642
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:14,000
Kêsek diçe cem te?
 
Has anyone come to you?

643
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:23,000
Erê, rehet bûne û ê qeçko jî, wek kuxkê qeçeko, îltîhabata
vêra... ew nexweşiyê heye.
 
Yes, they have gotten better, and also the children's...
like the children's cough, inflammation... those sicknesses
exist.

644
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:26,000
Ji dermaniya wî jî heye em çêdikin didin.
 
We also have medicine for that, we make it and give it.

645
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:27,000
Ê zaroka û jî?
 
And for children as well?

646
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:28,000
Ê zarokaye jî...
 
For the children as well...

647
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:30,000
Êna em çi dermanê ji te bixwazin tu kanî çêbikî?
 
If we ask you for any medicine, can you make it?

648
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:32,000
Çi bixwaze çêdibim.
 
Whatever they want, I can make it.

649
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:32,000
Erê.
 
And it works?

650
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:33,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

651
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:33,000
Çêdibe.
 
It works?

652
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:34,000
Çêdibe.
 
It works.

653
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:35,000
Ê milet pir tê ba te?
 
Do people come to you a lot?

654
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:43,000
Ê wele, na me go na, belaşe... em pera nabin, milet jî dibê
qey ev...izanî bo me na...tu ey pera werina.
 
Well, no, we told them it is free, we don't take money.
People think maybe they know about us, maybe they think you
will take money.

655
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:53,000
Em me jî em pera nabin li buwî ruhek şehîdê me, û miletî me,
em teberûhî vî tiştî dikin...eslen.
 
We don't take money, it is for the souls of our martyrs, and
for our people, we are doing this voluntarily... basically.

656
00:40:53,000 --> 00:40:54,000
Te cera pera nebirine?
 
Have you never taken money?

657
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:56,000
Na me nebirine, ji xatirê Xwedê...
 
No, we haven't taken it, for the sake of God...

658
00:40:56,000 --> 00:41:03,000
Baş e, zate ev xulqê gunda ev edebiyata gunda ev tişta îna
hetane namê mayî zate. Ev pirsa ev tişta ev edeta.
 
Alright, anyway this behavior of the villages, this
etiquette of the villages, these things have remained among
us until now anyway. These questions, these things, these
traditions.

659
00:41:03,000 --> 00:41:05,000
Ev pirsên berê pera ti nebûn.
 
These questions of the past, there was no money involved.

660
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:06,000
Ti nebûn, wekî te digot te jî...
 
There wasn't any, as you were saying you also...

661
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:17,000
Erê... cîran tiştek dida cîran nedigo ka bo... mesele mi
qebila genim te tişkî mida, ev tu kê çima bidî, çi te ti
neba min ê bita da ew yê min ti raba te bida min.
 
Yes... a neighbor would give something to a neighbor and
wouldn't say "where is the return"... for example if I gave
you a handful of wheat, you gave me something, why would you
give this, if you didn't have anything I would give it to
you, and when you had it you would give it to me.

662
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:21,000
Vê pare bûye...
 
Now it has become about money...

663
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:30,000
Ka anikê j'me re bahsê bike, evê ji bo çi tu hazir kiriye?
 
Come on now tell us, what have you prepared this for?

664
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:39,000
Eva guze, alem giy dizane... Erê guze... guze têda ha noka
teqrîben yanî berî bibin... hîn firîk in.
 
This is walnut, everyone knows... Yes, it is walnut...
walnut inside right now approximately meaning before they
ripen... they are still fresh.

665
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:42,000
Tê wê û eva jî baqil e.
 
You take that and this is broad beans.

666
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:51,000
Çiluwê baqile. Tê jê kî, û tê pelê guzê wa guzê gêndevo, wa
temarê urtiya piştê te jê derxînî.
 
It's the stems of the broad beans. You cut it, and you take
the walnut leaves, from that walnut tree, you take out the
veins from the back.

667
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:56,000
Tê xutkî, û tê di hewanekî de bikûtî.
 
You beat it, and you crush it in a mortar.

668
00:41:56,000 --> 00:42:06,000
Hebê sale birînik bê... destê te, lingê te, canê te tiştek
lê ew bê... tê bidiyê tavilê çêdikî.
 
If there's an Aleppo boil, or a wound... on your hand, your
leg, your body if there is something... you apply it to it
and you heal it immediately.

669
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:13,000
Eva... ê hebê sale û ê birîne vêye.
 
This... is for the Aleppo boil and wounds.

670
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:18,000
Eva gellek di malan giya da hebe.
 
This should be in many homes.

671
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:19,000
Ev li kî derê dibe?
 
Where does this grow?

672
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:21,000
Eva li gundên giya dibe.
 
This grows in all the villages.

673
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:22,000
Ev çi çêgiya meca?
 
What kind of grass is this?

674
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:35,000
Li qiraxa dibe, li ber mala dibe, ji nêv edera eva navê
gêndî de her ewok lehceyê xwe diguherîne yanî... gotinên xwe
diguherîne, em bi xwe dibên kinropek.
 
It grows on the edges, it grows near the houses, and in the
places of the threshing floors... this name in the village,
everyone changes their dialect meaning... they change their
words, we ourselves call it "kinropek".

675
00:42:35,000 --> 00:42:42,000
